node.title: All of today's coronavirus news in the one spot
node.description: Tasmania opens its borders and NSW further eases restrictions — get up to speed with all of the coronavirus news from across Australia in our COVID blog. Follow live.

node.title: Resource Management Act amendment passes final reading
node.description: Changes to the Resource Management Act making it easier to build houses in the country's biggest cities has passed its final reading in Parliament with cross-party support.

node.title: Inflation is whittling raises for frontline workers to "pennies"
node.description: Low-wage workers are enjoying some of the biggest pay gains in years. For many, it's still not a living wage.

node.title: ‘The Hand of God’ Review: A Portrait of the Cineaste as a Young Man
node.description: Paolo Sorrentino’s autobiographical drama about growing up in Naples is sensual, sad and occasionally sublime.

node.description: "She's a good cop," said Brooklyn Center Police Commander Garett Flesland while on the stand Tuesday,

node.title: Businesses says Northern Territory's new border rules will be another setback
node.description: Famed restaurateur Jimmy Shu will close his Darwin operation over Christmas for the first time, as travellers reconsider their plans to visit the Northern Territory amid restrictive border changes that come into effect next week.
